<Project Sdk="Microsoft.NET.Sdk">

  <!-- F050: the pure, value-only CONTENT-ADDRESSING BRIDGE. Two deterministic, total value transformations
       over the already-merged F032 vocabulary — `digestOf` (hash a gate's CAPTURED OUTPUT BYTES into the
       byte-stable `OutputDigest` F032 requires: SHA-256 over the raw bytes, lowercase hex, wrapped in the
       F032 `OutputDigest` newtype reused verbatim) and `recordOf` (assemble a complete F032 `CommandRecord`
       from a captured execution outcome by composing `digestOf` on the two output positions and DELEGATING
       the rest to `CommandRecord.build` VERBATIM).

       This is the FIRST and ONLY place in the codebase that hashes output bytes — precisely the gap F032 left
       open at D3 ("a supplied, already-computed digest … no hashing happens here"). The cache/evidence-reuse
       thread (F029-F049) can already sense freshness, evaluate reuse, embed verdicts, persist/bound/prune the
       store, derive an `EvidenceRef` from a `CommandRecord`, and fold it in — so the pure write path is
       complete FROM A `CommandRecord` ONWARD. But nothing produced a `CommandRecord` from a real execution:
       this row closes that last pure gap, mirroring how F047/F049 delivered the pure halves before their
       impure edges were wired.

       Both operations are PURE and TOTAL (FR-008): no I/O, no clock, no git, no environment, no network, no
       process; defined for every input — empty output bytes, binary/non-textual bytes, arbitrarily large
       bytes, a non-zero exit code, an applied timeout, an empty environment delta, and every captured-output
       outcome — never throwing. Hashing the supplied bytes is PURE computation, not I/O. `digestOf` is a
       function of byte CONTENT ONLY (FR-001/FR-002); `recordOf` is `build` composed with `digestOf` on the
       two output fields, NOTHING more (FR-004/FR-005) — no new record shape, no normalization, no
       reuse/success policy; the sensed duration is carried only in `record.Duration` and never read by the
       digest or the identity (FR-006). The digest scheme is FIXED and INTERNAL (FR-011) — not a policy knob.

       This row runs NO gate, senses NO fact, times NOTHING, persists NOTHING, bumps NO schema version, adds NO
       CLI, and introduces NO new type (it reuses F032 `OutputDigest`/`CommandRecord`/reproducible-fact
       vocabulary, `SensedDuration`, `CapturedOutput`, and the F014 `TimeoutLimit` verbatim) — so it carries
       only `ExecutionRecord.fsi` + `ExecutionRecord.fs`, no `Model` file. The IMPURE gate-execution port
       (spawning the process, reading real stdout/stderr, timing the run, sensing the facts) and the host
       wiring are the explicit FOLLOWING rows and are out of scope here; referenced by nothing on landing.

       It references ONLY FS.GG.Governance.CommandRecord (F032 `build`, `OutputDigest`, the reproducible-fact
       types, `SensedDuration`, `CapturedOutput`); FS.GG.Governance.Config (F014 `TimeoutLimit`) arrives
       TRANSITIVELY through F032. It adds NO new third-party PackageReference — the single new computation is a
       SHA-256 hash via `System.Security.Cryptography.SHA256.HashData` rendered with `System.Convert.ToHexString`,
       both BCL, both already used in the codebase (the F040 `Snapshot` interpreter). Compile order is
       ExecutionRecord.fsi -> ExecutionRecord.fs. The dependency direction stays one-way:
       ExecutionRecord -> CommandRecord -> Config. -->
  <PropertyGroup>
    <RootNamespace>FS.GG.Governance.ExecutionRecord</RootNamespace>
    <Version>0.1.0</Version>
    <!-- New package identity, packable like EvidenceCapture/CommandRecord/EvidenceReuseStore. "Pack output
         unaffected" means EXISTING packages are untouched, not that this library is unpackable. -->
    <IsPackable>true</IsPackable>
    <PackageId>FS.GG.Governance.ExecutionRecord</PackageId>
  </PropertyGroup>

  <ItemGroup>
    <Compile Include="ExecutionRecord.fsi" />
    <Compile Include="ExecutionRecord.fs" />
  </ItemGroup>

  <ItemGroup>
    <ProjectReference Include="../FS.GG.Governance.CommandRecord/FS.GG.Governance.CommandRecord.fsproj" />
  </ItemGroup>

</Project>
